Lemma 2.1. For a given non-negative initial conditions of state variables, there exists a unique solution SL, QL, EL, IL, ML, RL, SH, QH, EH, IH, MH, RHrespectively, for all time t ≥ 0. Moreover, The closed set:
D={(SL,QL,EL,IL,ML,RL,SH,QH,EH,IH,MH,RH)∈R+12:SL+QL+EL+IL+ML+RL+SH+QH+EH+IH+MH+RH≤πL+πHμ}
is positively invariant.
